        The forest is still again, nothing but that soft wind-breath through the leaves. But I saw it—I'm sure I saw it. The quiet feels different now, not peaceful—charged, aware. I'm not alone.

        I say, "Buddy, any life signs?"

        Buddy says, "No animals685 but the plants are reading really weird—like they're doing something? Should we name it? Naming things makes them less—"

