        Plants that move? But plants don't move like that—quick, purposeful, tracking—

        Except this is an alien planet—what if the plants here685

        Movement again—closer this time. Not threatening exactly, but deliberate, watching.

        I call, "Hello?"

        Nothing.

        ¶

        But I feel it—I feel watched. The forest isn't empty—something is out there in the purple twilight, curious, observing.

        Buddy says, "Kira? I think something's following us."

        My heart is racing, but also—this is the moment. My internal voice, Mav, says, «First contact begins with curiosity. Be curious back.»

